I need to implement _swim and _sink in min_pq.py. Let me explain each one and implement them with minimal changes.

_swim(k): Move element at position k up. In a min-heap, while k > 1 and parent (k//2) is greater than k, swap them and move up.

_sink(k): Move element at position k down. In a min-heap, while 2*k <= n (has children), find the smaller child, if k is greater than smaller child, swap and move down.

These are standard binary heap operations.

