What was changed and why
Only min_pq.py was edited. Two method bodies replaced their pass stubs:

_swim (line 149)

Loop condition k > 1: stop at the root (index 1).
self._greater(k // 2, k): if the parent is larger than the current node, the min-heap property is violated.
self._exch(k, k // 2) then k = k // 2: swap with parent and move up.
_sink (line 159)

Loop condition 2 * k <= self.n: stop when there are no children.
j = 2 * k picks the left child; if j < self.n and self._greater(j, j+1): j += 1 advances to the right child if it is smaller (so we always swap with the smaller child).
if not self._greater(k, j): break: stop if the current node is already ≤ its smaller child.
self._exch(k, j) then k = j: swap down and continue.
Both methods rely entirely on the pre-existing _greater (comparison, comparator-aware) and _exch (swap) helpers — no new imports or libraries introduced.

